---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="SkanPay - QR Checkout and Redemption Coordination"
  description="SkanPay helps stores and payment partners coordinate QR checkout requests, coupon or voucher redemption, customer approval, and merchant confirmation."
  activePath="/"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">QR payment gateway</p>
      <h1>Turn a QR scan into a checkout result</h1>
      <p class="hero-copy">
        SkanPay focuses on the layer stores actually need: a QR request the customer can approve, redemption logic when needed, and a clear result the merchant can trust.
      </p>
      <div class="button-row">
        <a class="button primary" href="/contact/">Contact SkanPay</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href="/qr-payments/">Explore Technology</a>
      </div>
      <div class="trust-strip" aria-label="SkanPay focus areas">
        <div class="trust-item">
          <strong>01</strong>
          Merchant status
        </div>
        <div class="trust-item">
          <strong>02</strong>
          Customer approval
        </div>
        <div class="trust-item">
          <strong>03</strong>
          Redemption logic
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <aside class="hero-panel" aria-label="SkanPay platform overview">
      <div class="panel-header">
        <span>Platform overview</span>
        <strong>SkanPay</strong>
      </div>
      <div class="system-card">
        <div>
          <span>Merchant problem</span>
          <strong>Staff need a readable payment state</strong>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span>Customer problem</span>
          <strong>Approval should happen in a familiar app flow</strong>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span>Partner problem</span>
          <strong>Coupons and vouchers need real-time coordination</strong>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span>SkanPay focus</span>
          <strong>Coordinate request, redemption, decision, and result</strong>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="signal-grid">
        <div><span>Flow</span><strong>QR request</strong></div>
        <div><span>Status</span><strong>Readable</strong></div>
        <div><span>Audience</span><strong>B2B</strong></div>
        <div><span>Scope</span><strong>Gateway</strong></div>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Problem and solution</p>
        <h2>QR payment needs more than a code on the counter</h2>
      </div>
      <p>
        SkanPay focuses on the operating layer between merchants, customers, payment apps, and redemption systems.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="pain-grid compact-grid">
      <article class="pain-card">
        <span>Merchant</span>
        <h3>Clear checkout status</h3>
        <p>Staff need to know whether a request was scanned, approved, cancelled, expired, or completed.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="pain-card">
        <span>Customer</span>
        <h3>Familiar scan-and-approve flow</h3>
        <p>The customer opens a QR request, reviews the details, and confirms through a supported app experience.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="pain-card">
        <span>Partner</span>
        <h3>Defined app participation</h3>
        <p>Wallet, payment, e-commerce, and loyalty apps need a clear role in the checkout handoff.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="pain-card">
        <span>Redemption</span>
        <h3>Coupon and voucher coordination</h3>
        <p>Promotions need to be validated without making checkout harder for staff or customers.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section technical-band">
    <div class="process-layout">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Flow</p>
        <h2>Merchant request to store result</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">
          The SkanPay model keeps the payment and redemption conversation readable for the store and structured for partners.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="skanpay-diagram" aria-label="SkanPay checkout flow">
        <div class="diagram-node merchant">
          <span>Merchant</span>
          <strong>Create QR request</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="diagram-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
        <div class="diagram-node customer">
          <span>Customer</span>
          <strong>Scan and approve</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="diagram-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
        <div class="diagram-node app">
          <span>Payment app</span>
          <strong>Authorize decision</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="diagram-result">
          <span>Store result</span>
          <strong>Confirmed / redeemed / cancelled / expired</strong>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section demo-preview">
    <div class="demo-preview-copy">
      <img class="beamcash-wordmark" src="/beamcash/beamcash-wordmark.svg" alt="BeamCash" />
      <p class="eyebrow">Demo proof</p>
      <h2>BeamCash makes the checkout flow tangible</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">
        BeamCash is the working demo used to show seller QR setup and buyer checkout before a deeper SkanPay integration conversation.
      </p>
      <a class="button primary" href="/beamcash-demo/">View Demo</a>
    </div>
    <div class="demo-screens" aria-label="BeamCash demo screens">
      <figure>
        <img src="/beamcash/beamcash-seller-dashboard-mobile.png" alt="BeamCash seller dashboard with QR code" />
        <figcaption>Seller QR dashboard</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure>
        <img src="/beamcash/beamcash-buyer-checkout-mobile.png" alt="BeamCash buyer checkout screen" />
        <figcaption>Buyer checkout</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-band">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Next step</p>
      <h2>Bring QR payment conversations into focus.</h2>
      <p>Share the merchant, partner, or product details you want SkanPay to support and the team can follow up directly.</p>
    </div>
    <a class="button secondary" href="/contact/">Start a Conversation</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
